cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel neural network nonlinearity for disentangling core concepts in neural networks, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their core concepts. The next likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper specifically mentions disentangling concepts within 3D scene representations. The paper also mentions natural language narratives, which suggests it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper's use of hyper-dimensional computing theory suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
